🕸️ Web Scraper and Summarizer
Created by Kaustubh Bhalerao

🌟 Overview
This project combines web scraping and AI-based summarization to extract content from websites and generate concise, insightful summaries — all in one streamlined process. It’s designed to cut through irrelevant content like ads, navigation links, and scripts, leaving only the core information.

✨ Features
Web Scraping: Uses requests and BeautifulSoup4 to fetch, clean, and parse content from any website.
AI-Powered Summarization: Built with Hugging Face’s T5-small model to generate clear, high-quality summaries.
Custom Prompting: Integrates langchain to create structured prompts, ensuring irrelevant content is ignored while the essential details are captured.
Markdown Output: Generates clean, readable summaries — perfect for research, news aggregation, or quick content digestion.
🔧 Tech Stack
Python
requests, BeautifulSoup4 (for web scraping)
transformers (T5-small) and torch (for summarization)
langchain (for content loading and structured prompt handling)
🚀 How to Use
Install dependencies:

pip install transformers torch beautifulsoup4 langchain-community
Run the summarizer:
Import the function and provide a URL:

from webscrapersummarizer import summarize  
print(summarize("https://example.com"))
Get your AI-generated summary — clean, short, and easy to read!

🔥 Future Improvements
Support for multi-page scraping
More summarization models (e.g., BART, GPT)
Improved content filtering
CLI support for faster usage
